Here's the full API reference for both catalogs:

  ---
  Catalog API Reference

  Base URL: https://<your-api-host>
  Auth: All endpoints require the header x-admin-key: <CATALOG_ADMIN_KEY>
  Caching: All responses are cached for 12 hours. First request after cache expiry hits the database; subsequent requests are served from Redis.

  ---
  Alternatives Catalog

  1. GET /alternatives/catalog/categories

  Returns all distinct category values for SaaS apps that have at least one enriched alternative. Use these to populate a category filter UI.

  Headers
  x-admin-key: <key>

  Response 200
  {
    "data": ["CRM", "Help Desk", "Project Management"],
    "total": 3
  }

  ┌───────┬──────────┬───────────────────────────────┐
  │ Field │   Type   │          Description          │
  ├───────┼──────────┼───────────────────────────────┤
  │ data  │ string[] │ Sorted list of category names │
  ├───────┼──────────┼───────────────────────────────┤
  │ total │ number   │ Count of distinct categories  │
  └───────┴──────────┴───────────────────────────────┘

  ---
  2. GET /alternatives/catalog

  Returns SaaS apps that have at least one enriched alternative, with their alternatives nested. Supports pagination and optional grouping.

  Query params

  ┌───────────────┬────────┬──────────┬──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
  │     Param     │  Type  │ Required │                             Description                              │
  ├───────────────┼────────┼──────────┼──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
  │ take          │ number │ No       │ Page size. Default: 10                                               │
  ├───────────────┼────────┼──────────┼──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
  │ skip          │ number │ No       │ Offset. Default: 0. Ignored when cursor is set                       │
  ├───────────────┼────────┼──────────┼──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
  │ cursor        │ string │ No       │ ID of the last item from the previous page (cursor-based pagination) │
  ├───────────────┼────────┼──────────┼──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
  │ category      │ string │ No       │ Filter by source app category (exact match)                          │
  ├───────────────┼────────┼──────────┼──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
  │ source_app_id │ string │ No       │ Return alternatives for a single app by its ID                       │
  ├───────────────┼────────┼──────────┼──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
  │ grouped       │ "true" │ No       │ When "true", groups results by category key                          │
  └───────────────┴────────┴──────────┴──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

  Pagination — skip/take
  GET /alternatives/catalog?take=10&skip=0
  GET /alternatives/catalog?take=10&skip=10

  Pagination — cursor (recommended for large datasets)
  GET /alternatives/catalog?take=10
  # use nextCursor from response:
  GET /alternatives/catalog?take=10&cursor=<nextCursor>

